0 -14 Td
(Owner: Facilities Reliability Team) Tj
0 -14 Td
(Applies To: North Campus Distribution Operations) Tj
0 -14 Td
(Review Cycle: Every 12 months or after equipment redesign) Tj
0 -14 Td
() Tj
0 -14 Td
(PURPOSE) Tj
0 -14 Td
() Tj
0 -14 Td
(This procedure defines the monthly preventive maintenance routine for the fictional CNV-220) Tj
0 -14 Td
(takeaway conveyor used in the packing mezzanine. The goal is to catch belt tracking drift,) Tj
0 -14 Td
(worn rollers, loose guards, and overheating drive components before they interrupt outbound) Tj
0 -14 Td
(volume.) Tj
0 -14 Td
() Tj
0 -14 Td
(The procedure is intended for trained maintenance technicians and shift leads. Production) Tj
0 -14 Td
(operators may assist with observation and restart confirmation, but they do not perform) Tj
0 -14 Td
(isolated service work unless the task card explicitly allows it.) Tj
0 -14 Td
() Tj
0 -14 Td
(REQUIRED TOOLS AND PARTS) Tj
0 -14 Td
() Tj
0 -14 Td
(- Lockout kit with personal lock, hasp, and danger tag.) Tj
0 -14 Td
(- Infrared thermometer, 6 mm hex key set, belt tension gauge, flashlight, clean lint-free) Tj
0 -14 Td
(cloths.) Tj
0 -14 Td
(- Approved replacement hardware for side guards, nose pulley fasteners, and three standard) Tj
0 -14 Td
(return rollers.) Tj
0 -14 Td
(- Work order printout or digital task card showing the exact conveyor zone and last completed) Tj
0 -14 Td
(service date.) Tj
0 -14 Td
() Tj
0 -14 Td
(HAZARDS AND CONTROLS) Tj
0 -14 Td
() Tj
0 -14 Td
(- Treat the conveyor as energized until lockout is verified at the local disconnect and start) Tj
0 -14 Td
(button.) Tj
0 -14 Td
(- Keep both side guards installed unless a specific inspection step calls for temporary) Tj
0 -14 Td
(removal and reinstall them before manual jogging.) Tj
0 -14 Td
(- Do not place hands between the belt and roller bed while checking tracking; use a marked) Tj
0 -14 Td
(reference point and observe from the frame edge.) Tj
0 -14 Td
(- If product debris contains broken glass, use cut-resistant gloves and dispose of waste in) Tj
0 -14 Td
(the designated rigid container.) Tj
0 -14 Td
() Tj
0 -14 Td
(PREPARATION) Tj
0 -14 Td
() Tj
0 -14 Td
(- Confirm the service window with the area lead and post a maintenance in progress sign at) Tj
0 -14 Td
(both feeder points.) Tj
ET
endstream
