(- Stop the conveyor from the local HMI, isolate the disconnect, apply personal lockout, and) Tj
0 -14 Td
(test the start station for zero response.) Tj
0 -14 Td
(- Walk the full conveyor length and inspect belt edges, splice condition, side guides, frame) Tj
0 -14 Td
(welds, and return roller rotation.) Tj
0 -14 Td
(- Clean the nose pulley, tail pulley, photo-eye brackets, and debris traps. Note any product) Tj
0 -14 Td
(residue that could change tracking or sensor performance.) Tj
0 -14 Td
(- Measure motor surface temperature and gearbox housing temperature before adjustment. Compare) Tj
0 -14 Td
(readings to the baseline values in the task card.) Tj
0 -14 Td
(- Check belt tracking by hand-jogging only after all guards are temporarily reinstalled and) Tj
0 -14 Td
(the area is clear. If the belt drifts more than 5 mm at either edge, adjust the tail tracking) Tj
0 -14 Td
(bolts in quarter-turn increments.) Tj
0 -14 Td
(- Verify roller condition by spinning each return roller. Replace any roller that binds,) Tj
0 -14 Td
(chatters, or has visible flat spots.) Tj
0 -14 Td
(- Re-tension the belt only if the gauge reading falls outside the approved operating band of) Tj
0 -14 Td
(32 to 36 units.) Tj
0 -14 Td
(- Restore the system, remove lockout, run the conveyor empty for three minutes, then run ten) Tj
0 -14 Td
(sample cartons through the full path.) Tj
0 -14 Td
() Tj
0 -14 Td
(PROCEDURE) Tj
0 -14 Td
() Tj
0 -14 Td
(- Belt tracks within 5 mm of centerline at empty and loaded conditions.) Tj
0 -14 Td
(- No exposed hardware, missing guards, or loose brackets remain after service.) Tj
0 -14 Td
(- Motor and gearbox temperatures are stable and do not exceed the prior baseline by more than) Tj
0 -14 Td
(8 C.) Tj
0 -14 Td
(- Ten sample cartons pass without skewing, snagging, or photo-eye interruption faults.) Tj
0 -14 Td
() Tj
0 -14 Td
(ACCEPTANCE CRITERIA) Tj
0 -14 Td
() Tj
0 -14 Td
(- Record as-found and as-left belt tension readings in the work order.) Tj
0 -14 Td
(- List every adjusted component, replaced roller, and reused spare part by quantity.) Tj
0 -14 Td
(- If a defect is deferred, create a follow-up corrective work order and note the risk to) Tj
0 -14 Td
(throughput.) Tj
0 -14 Td
(- Obtain shift lead sign-off after the loaded restart test is complete.) Tj
0 -14 Td
() Tj
0 -14 Td
(RECORDS AND CLOSEOUT) Tj
0 -14 Td
() Tj
0 -14 Td
(- A common failure pattern on this fictional conveyor is gradual drift toward the operator) Tj
0 -14 Td
(side after two weeks of heavy carton volume. In past simulations, the root cause was usually) Tj
0 -14 Td
(tail roller contamination rather than major frame damage.) Tj
0 -14 Td
(- Technicians should avoid overcorrecting tracking with large bolt turns. Small adjustments) Tj
0 -14 Td
(followed by an empty run and a loaded run give more repeatable results and make later) Tj
0 -14 Td
(troubleshooting easier.) Tj
0 -14 Td
(- When reviewing the service log, compare temperature data by season. Ambient heat on the) Tj
0 -14 Td
(mezzanine can raise baseline readings in summer without indicating a drive failure.) Tj
0 -14 Td
() Tj
0 -14 Td
(EXAMPLES AND NOTES) Tj
0 -14 Td
() Tj
